  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Oversee and manage comprehensive accounting functions, delivering accurate financial reports and analyses to drive strategic business decisions and enhance financial processes.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead the full set of accounts management and execute month-end closing to ensure timely financial closure</li><li>Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial reports with accuracy to support business transparency and compliance</li><li>Manage budgeting, forecasting, and financial planning processes to align financial goals with business strategy</li><li>Monitor cash flow, expenses, and overall financial performance to inform and support effective business decisions</li><li>Ensure adherence to accounting standards, company policies, and statutory requirements to maintain regulatory compliance</li><li>Coordinate with auditors, tax agents, banks, and other external parties to facilitate smooth financial operations</li><li>Provide detailed financial analysis and insights to management to support strategic planning and business growth</li><li>Identify and implement improvements in financial processes, controls, and reporting efficiency to optimize operations</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field</li><li>Minimum 5 years of relevant experience in finance or accounting</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in managing a team</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office, especially Excel</li><li>Strong knowledge of accounting standards and financial reporting</li><li>Demonstrated analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills</li><li>Ability to work independently and meet tight deadlines</li></ul>",
